---

## Mandatory Rules

### MUST

- Use one schema per microservice.
- Use UUID primary keys.
- Include tenant and audit columns on business tables.
- Manage every schema change with Flyway.
- Store binary files in S3 and metadata in PostgreSQL.
- Store embeddings in pgvector.
- Keep Outbox and Inbox tables within the owning service.
- Search the repository before creating new database objects.

### MUST NOT

- Share databases across microservices.
- Create cross-service foreign keys.
- Store large binary objects in PostgreSQL.
- Modify applied Flyway migrations.
- Duplicate business data across services.
- Store secrets or passwords in plain text.
- Bypass aggregate ownership.
- Let Platform Core own industry-specific tables.

---

